WEBVTT

00:03.071 --> 00:06.874
Jenny, if you keep going after
them, they're gonna kill you.

00:06.907 --> 00:08.042
We need to tidy
your mess.

00:08.076 --> 00:10.544
Scarlet.
Where is she?

00:10.578 --> 00:11.579
I don't know.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.781
No! No!

00:16.450 --> 00:18.986
I have feelers out
for Scarlet and Phoebe.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.921
Figure they have to
resurface at some point.

00:20.954 --> 00:22.390
Yeah, definitely.
Keep me posted.

00:22.423 --> 00:24.392
Jag: Last I checked,
Dad still calls the shots.

00:24.425 --> 00:26.060
Ren: Could confront him.
No.

00:26.094 --> 00:27.828
You're right.
We're way past talking.

00:27.861 --> 00:30.531
Dad's getting old -- he's making
questionable choices.

00:30.564 --> 00:32.666
You want
to force Dad out?

00:32.700 --> 00:35.002
Do we have a choice?
It's gonna have to
come from me.

00:35.035 --> 00:37.838
I just need you to tell me
who runs the Bhullar Cartel.

00:37.871 --> 00:40.040
[ Grunts ]

00:40.074 --> 00:42.076
[ Gunshot ]

00:42.110 --> 00:43.944
Turns out Alicia
is a lawyer,

00:43.977 --> 00:47.581
and she paid the sheriff
a little visit after that raid.

00:47.615 --> 00:49.417
More than
likely she's gonna end up dead

00:49.450 --> 00:51.419
like the, uh,
waitress in Seattle.

00:51.452 --> 00:52.620
That's the second time
you've mentioned her.

00:52.653 --> 00:54.021
Do you wanna
tell me something?

00:54.054 --> 00:55.623
Hey, can I help you,
friend?

00:55.656 --> 00:57.691
I certainly hope so.

00:57.725 --> 00:58.559
[ Gun cocks ]

01:00.994 --> 01:02.730
I'm here to meet
Veer Bhullar.

01:05.833 --> 01:08.068
[ Monitor beeping ]

01:10.671 --> 01:12.940
How is he?

01:12.973 --> 01:16.544
Sedated.
He'll be fine.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.479
[ Sighs ]

01:21.149 --> 01:22.483
Now he just needs
his rest.

01:22.516 --> 01:24.318
If you don't mind.

01:24.352 --> 01:26.086
I actually wanna be here
when he wakes up.

01:26.120 --> 01:28.322
I don't think
that's such a good idea.

01:28.356 --> 01:30.724
No, it's okay.
I'm -- I'm gonna stick around.

01:30.758 --> 01:33.060
I understand how you feel,
Miss Hoyt.

01:33.093 --> 01:35.463
How do you know
my name?

01:35.496 --> 01:37.331
Oh. Small town.

01:39.133 --> 01:41.169
I like to know
who's looking out for us.

01:43.504 --> 01:46.006
That's good.

01:46.039 --> 01:47.475
I'm still gonna
stick around.

01:49.543 --> 01:52.946
Well...

01:52.980 --> 01:55.516
I'll give you two
some time then.

01:55.549 --> 02:02.556
**

02:03.891 --> 02:07.161
[ Monitor beeping ]

02:07.195 --> 02:09.697
Ma'am, no one's supposed
to be in this room.

02:09.730 --> 02:11.465
Oh, it's okay.

02:11.499 --> 02:12.966
I've already talked
to the other nurse.

02:13.000 --> 02:14.802
I'm the only one
on the wing tonight.

02:14.835 --> 02:21.842
**

02:23.143 --> 02:30.150
**

02:31.319 --> 02:38.326
**

02:39.560 --> 02:41.929
[ Airplane engine whirring ]

02:53.106 --> 02:54.775
[ Vehicle door opens ]

02:58.212 --> 02:59.913
[ Yawns ]

02:59.947 --> 03:01.148
Finally.

03:01.181 --> 03:02.049
Been waiting all night.

03:03.884 --> 03:04.718
Gonna sit in front.

03:12.626 --> 03:14.262
Jag: Everything okay?

03:14.295 --> 03:15.696
How do you mean?

03:15.729 --> 03:18.232
Well, you went to see Stewart,
right?

03:18.266 --> 03:20.734
About the financials?

03:20.768 --> 03:22.670
Mm-hmm.

03:22.703 --> 03:24.872
You do know there's
this thing called Zoom, right?

03:24.905 --> 03:26.774
Jag,
that's you chattering.

03:26.807 --> 03:30.244
Just like you did
when you were little

03:30.278 --> 03:31.945
and you wanted
another biscuit.

03:31.979 --> 03:34.482
You knew the answer.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.686
Why don't you just ask
for the biscuit, son?

03:38.719 --> 03:40.321
We both know who cut the drugs,
okay?

03:42.623 --> 03:44.758
And?

03:44.792 --> 03:46.093
Why did you do it?

03:47.094 --> 03:48.796
Was it about the money?

03:48.829 --> 03:50.598
It's always
about the money.

03:50.631 --> 03:52.466
Okay, great.

03:52.500 --> 03:54.768
Now, is there something else
you would like to discuss?

03:54.802 --> 03:56.804
Me and Ren think
that you should take a step back

03:56.837 --> 03:58.138
from running things.

03:58.171 --> 04:00.774
Ah, you and Ren. Okay.

04:00.808 --> 04:02.276
We've been worried
about some of the decisions

04:02.310 --> 04:05.446
you've been making.
Don't you challenge

04:05.479 --> 04:11.051
my decisions,
you spoiled little brat.

04:11.084 --> 04:12.420
You need to step down.

04:13.954 --> 04:16.957
My God.

04:16.990 --> 04:20.093
Did she actually
put you up to this?

04:20.127 --> 04:22.530
No, she didn't, Dad.

04:24.432 --> 04:25.766
It was our decision
together.

04:25.799 --> 04:27.635
Just like the move
to Montana was?

04:27.668 --> 04:34.675
**

04:34.975 --> 04:41.982
**

04:42.350 --> 04:45.686
Make me some chai,
son.

04:45.719 --> 04:47.788
And then find
your sister.

04:47.821 --> 04:50.324
A good airing of grievances
is just what...

04:50.358 --> 04:53.761
**

04:53.794 --> 04:55.195
Where is my daughter?

04:55.228 --> 04:57.665
Are you the man
in charge?

04:57.698 --> 05:00.368
I'm thinkin'
that ya are.

05:00.401 --> 05:04.271
What have you done
with my daughter?

05:04.304 --> 05:06.574
Okay, I'm gonna need you
to stop.

05:08.509 --> 05:09.610
[ Gun cocks ]

05:09.643 --> 05:10.811
Please?

05:10.844 --> 05:13.013
Dad, do what he says.

05:13.046 --> 05:14.548
Ah, listen to your son.

05:14.582 --> 05:16.817
My son is a fool.

05:16.850 --> 05:20.821
Well,
the three of us --

05:20.854 --> 05:22.155
we're taking a ride.

05:22.189 --> 05:27.194
**

05:28.429 --> 05:29.797
Cassie: Tubb's gonna be okay,
though, right?

05:29.830 --> 05:31.164
[ Sighs ] I hope so.

05:31.198 --> 05:32.800
He was still out of it
when I left.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.568
Ah, he'll be fine. It's not
the first time he's been shot.

05:36.704 --> 05:38.238
Something else
bothering you?

05:38.271 --> 05:39.840
There was a weird guy
in Tubb's room.

05:39.873 --> 05:41.341
Weird how?

05:41.375 --> 05:43.644
He said he was a nurse,
but he wasn't.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.979
You think he could have been
connected to the cartel?

05:46.013 --> 05:48.382
I-I put a guard on his room,
just in case.

05:48.416 --> 05:49.983
Smart.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.585
Okay, let's focus
on the current problem.

05:51.619 --> 05:53.421
Where's Richard?

05:53.454 --> 05:56.089
No, I still cannot believe
that he would ever shoot a cop.

05:56.123 --> 05:58.426
That is not the guy
that I thought I knew.

05:58.459 --> 06:01.429
Well, grief affects us
in ways we can't predict.

06:01.462 --> 06:03.697
Richard thinks
the police failed him.

06:03.731 --> 06:07.100
So, we've gotta find him
before he hurts anybody else.

06:07.134 --> 06:09.503
Or before one of my deputies
tries to get payback.

06:09.537 --> 06:12.005
Okay, so, first goes
to Mason's friend,

06:12.039 --> 06:13.874
then Dietrich,
then Tubb.

06:13.907 --> 06:15.108
He's clearly
on a mission.

06:16.910 --> 06:19.613
Sooner or later he's gonna show
up on the Bhullars' doorstep.

06:19.647 --> 06:21.682
He could be there
right now.

06:21.715 --> 06:24.284
Only one way to find out.

06:24.317 --> 06:31.324
**

06:31.492 --> 06:32.693
[ Engine shuts off ]

06:32.726 --> 06:37.865
**

06:37.898 --> 06:40.100
Travis' truck.

06:40.133 --> 06:41.735
We didn't exactly creep
in here.

06:41.769 --> 06:43.704
Where's the welcome wagon?

06:43.737 --> 06:44.772
Look.

06:44.805 --> 06:47.475
I don't like this.

06:47.508 --> 06:52.245
**

06:52.279 --> 06:53.881
This count
for probable cause?

06:53.914 --> 06:55.483
Guess we'll find out.

06:55.516 --> 07:02.523
**

07:05.258 --> 07:06.560
Clear.

07:06.594 --> 07:09.563
**

07:09.597 --> 07:10.998
Police!

07:11.031 --> 07:12.566
Anybody here?!

07:12.600 --> 07:13.634
Ren: Up here!

07:13.667 --> 07:20.674
**

07:22.776 --> 07:24.344
What happened?

07:24.377 --> 07:26.747
Some guy came in here
with a gun.

07:26.780 --> 07:29.116
The kind of criminals
you should be focused on.

07:29.149 --> 07:30.484
Yeah,
we know who he is.

07:30.518 --> 07:32.119
Oh, great.

07:32.152 --> 07:33.654
Well, he clocked Stone
and he handcuffed us.

07:33.687 --> 07:35.856
You okay?

07:35.889 --> 07:37.324
Hello.

07:37.357 --> 07:38.959
This guy has my father
and my brother.

07:38.992 --> 07:40.728
Where'd he take them?

07:42.162 --> 07:44.331
To get ice cream.
How am I supposed to know?

07:44.364 --> 07:45.232
I think I know where.

07:46.734 --> 07:48.368
Let's go.
Wait!

07:48.401 --> 07:50.137
Aren't you gonna let us go?

07:52.573 --> 07:54.942
I prefer you
with your hands tied.

07:54.975 --> 07:57.545
Every time I take my eyes
off you, another body drops.

07:57.578 --> 08:04.585
**

08:06.520 --> 08:08.388
[ Gun cocks ]

08:11.091 --> 08:12.392
Get out.

08:12.425 --> 08:15.128
Walk around
and open his door.

08:15.162 --> 08:18.532
If you try and run,
I'll shoot him.

08:18.566 --> 08:20.801
**

08:20.834 --> 08:22.335
Where are you taking us?

08:22.369 --> 08:27.074
Oh, my son,
his life ended right up there.

08:28.241 --> 08:31.078
And that's where
your lives are gonna end.

08:36.950 --> 08:39.019
Tell me why I'm trying
to stop this.

08:39.052 --> 08:41.521
The Bhullars are monsters.

08:41.555 --> 08:46.426
Richard would be doing me,
doing the entire town, a favor.

08:46.459 --> 08:48.195
That's not who you are.

08:48.228 --> 08:50.230
That's not who I am.

08:50.263 --> 08:53.500
I want no part
in thinking that way.

08:53.533 --> 08:55.168
We stop all of this,
no matter what.

08:55.202 --> 08:57.504
The Bhullars
need to go down.

08:57.537 --> 09:00.240
Maybe you and Travis
can figure out how.

09:00.273 --> 09:03.010
[ Chuckles ] I'm not so sure
we're on the same team anymore.

09:03.043 --> 09:06.947
Then do something.
Try to get through to him.

09:06.980 --> 09:10.283
Right now, the only thing
I can hope for

09:10.317 --> 09:13.420
is that he gets
out of this mess alive.

09:14.588 --> 09:16.523
[ Sighs ]

09:16.556 --> 09:23.563
**

09:25.799 --> 09:27.167
What was his name?

09:29.136 --> 09:31.571
Your son.

09:31.605 --> 09:32.740
Mason.

09:32.773 --> 09:34.908
Mason was weak,
I take it?

09:34.942 --> 09:36.777
People who do drugs are.

09:36.810 --> 09:38.111
Mason wasn't weak.

09:38.145 --> 09:39.747
But it was his choice
to do drugs.

09:39.780 --> 09:41.815
No one forced him to.

09:41.849 --> 09:46.720
But I-I understand why you're
looking for someone to blame.

09:46.754 --> 09:49.790
I know.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.125
I know what it is
to have a weak son.

09:53.961 --> 09:56.764
Only so much
we fathers can do.

09:56.797 --> 10:00.267
The choice was his.

10:00.300 --> 10:02.135
Listen, we have money.

10:04.805 --> 10:06.940
I know that's not gonna
bring your son back,

10:06.974 --> 10:09.576
but...

10:09.609 --> 10:14.347
if you walk away
and let us go...

10:14.381 --> 10:15.949
you'll be compensated.

10:15.983 --> 10:18.118
Money?

10:18.151 --> 10:20.921
Well, at this point,
what else is there?

10:20.954 --> 10:22.622
Now you have a choice.

10:24.191 --> 10:25.659
Make the wise one.

10:25.693 --> 10:26.727
Choice.

10:28.962 --> 10:30.363
How 'bout this?

10:30.397 --> 10:33.300
Which one of you...

10:33.333 --> 10:35.302
am I gonna kill first?

10:35.335 --> 10:37.304
**

10:37.337 --> 10:39.139
You...

10:39.172 --> 10:42.042
**

10:42.075 --> 10:43.677
...or your son?

10:43.711 --> 10:49.549
**

10:49.582 --> 10:51.451
Keep walking.

10:51.484 --> 10:53.854
**

10:53.887 --> 10:55.322
Mm.

10:59.359 --> 11:00.193
What?

11:02.395 --> 11:04.031
I'm thinking
we do this now.

11:06.033 --> 11:08.368
Do what?
I show you mine,
you show me yours.

11:08.401 --> 11:09.703
We'll swap secrets.

11:12.906 --> 11:14.842
I don't know
what you're talking about.
Okay, I'll go first.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.377
Major vibes
with blondie.

11:19.780 --> 11:21.081
Again, no idea.

11:21.114 --> 11:23.383
I know you're a cop,
Stone.

11:23.416 --> 11:28.221
Stone, ugh,
such a stupid, macho name.

11:28.255 --> 11:29.689
I hate that I thought
it was hot.

11:29.723 --> 11:32.392
What do I --
What do I have to do?

11:32.425 --> 11:33.861
Like, kill another person
in front of you

11:33.894 --> 11:35.495
to prove my loyalty,
what?

11:35.528 --> 11:37.931
Right, Mr. Bob with the knife
in his throat.

11:37.965 --> 11:40.700
That just bought you time.

11:40.734 --> 11:43.370
I just kept asking myself,
"Well -- Well, if he's a cop,

11:43.403 --> 11:45.405
then why haven't
I been arrested?

11:45.438 --> 11:46.439
It's not like
he hasn't seen anything."

11:46.473 --> 11:48.275
No, you'd seen too much.

11:48.308 --> 11:50.110
I kept going back and forth
with myself.

11:50.143 --> 11:53.947
Then you asked
about the girl.

11:53.981 --> 11:57.017
Then it all clicked.

11:57.050 --> 11:59.586
Kate Garza.

12:00.954 --> 12:03.423
I looked into her.

12:03.456 --> 12:04.758
She wasn't just
my dad's girlfriend,

12:04.792 --> 12:08.896
she was an informant.

12:08.929 --> 12:11.698
And my dad found out
and she disappeared

12:11.731 --> 12:13.901
and now you want to know
what happened to her.

12:15.468 --> 12:17.704
Isn't that right...

12:17.737 --> 12:19.706
Travis?

12:19.739 --> 12:25.745
**

12:25.779 --> 12:28.481
Well, Ren,
if you know all that,

12:28.515 --> 12:29.682
why am I still breathing?

12:33.086 --> 12:34.654
That is the question,
isn't it?

12:34.687 --> 12:41.261
**

12:41.294 --> 12:47.300
**

12:47.334 --> 12:50.337
We're gonna do this
my way now.

12:50.370 --> 12:52.105
And what way is that?

12:54.507 --> 12:56.009
Alright, stop.

12:56.043 --> 12:57.010
Right there.

12:57.044 --> 12:59.012
**

12:59.046 --> 13:01.849
Look, I'm sorry.

13:01.882 --> 13:03.783
Okay?

13:03.817 --> 13:05.152
We're both very sorry.

13:05.185 --> 13:06.153
Down on your knees.

13:06.186 --> 13:12.425
**

13:12.459 --> 13:13.793
Both of ya.

13:16.897 --> 13:17.865
This isn't you.

13:17.898 --> 13:19.699
You don't know anything.

13:19.732 --> 13:22.335
I know
that you're not a killer.

13:22.369 --> 13:24.337
Right?
Not before.

13:24.371 --> 13:27.374
But you turned me
into one.

13:27.407 --> 13:31.544
**

13:31.578 --> 13:32.479
There's his car.

13:32.512 --> 13:38.485
**

13:38.518 --> 13:40.487
This...
[ Gun cocks ]

13:40.520 --> 13:42.155
...is for Mason.

13:42.189 --> 13:44.557
Please. Look,
you're gonna regret this

13:44.591 --> 13:45.959
for the rest
of your life.

13:45.993 --> 13:47.327
At least I'll know
I did something

13:47.360 --> 13:49.329
to stop another kid
from dying.

13:49.362 --> 13:51.164
Then just kill my son.

13:53.233 --> 13:56.303
He's the one responsible
for your son's death.

13:56.336 --> 13:59.006
He's the one
in charge of everything.

13:59.039 --> 14:00.473
Isn't that right,
Jagat?

14:00.507 --> 14:06.880
**

14:06.914 --> 14:08.381
What --
What are you doing?

14:08.415 --> 14:11.084
I'm getting up
so I can walk away

14:11.118 --> 14:13.320
and forget
that I ever saw you.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.655
Get back on your knees.
I think not.

14:15.688 --> 14:17.891
You're not gonna
do anything.

14:17.925 --> 14:19.592
Dad?
I'll shoot!

14:19.626 --> 14:20.427
I will!

14:20.460 --> 14:21.561
Dad!

14:21.594 --> 14:22.729
[ Screams ]

14:22.762 --> 14:24.764
[ Gunshot ]

14:24.797 --> 14:26.266
[ Body thuds ]

14:26.299 --> 14:32.005
**

14:32.039 --> 14:37.710
**

14:43.583 --> 14:47.887
**

14:47.921 --> 14:49.256
Jenny: Drop the gun!

14:49.289 --> 14:51.024
**

14:51.058 --> 14:52.092
Now, Richard!

14:52.125 --> 14:53.460
Richard: I'm sorry.

14:53.493 --> 14:55.262
I'm -- I'm gonna
go see Mason now.

14:55.295 --> 14:56.896
Richard, just -- don't!

14:56.930 --> 14:59.132
Richard.
Richard, look at me.

15:00.633 --> 15:02.302
Think of Mona.

15:02.335 --> 15:04.304
Mona needs your help.

15:04.337 --> 15:06.106
Don't bring my wife
into this.

15:06.139 --> 15:08.175
My wife is innocent.

15:10.277 --> 15:11.311
Richard.

15:11.344 --> 15:14.214
[ Sighs ]

15:14.247 --> 15:16.816
The drugs Mason took,
they were hers.

15:19.953 --> 15:21.454
No.

15:21.488 --> 15:24.591
No, that ca--
that can't be true.

15:24.624 --> 15:26.293
Yes, it is, and she needs you
to forgive her.

15:26.326 --> 15:28.161
No. No.

15:28.195 --> 15:30.363
Okay, Richard,
look at me.

15:32.765 --> 15:34.267
Your daughter needs you.

15:34.301 --> 15:35.735
Please.

15:35.768 --> 15:36.903
Richard.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.772
**

15:39.806 --> 15:41.408
A girl needs her father.

15:41.441 --> 15:44.011
And I know this
because I lost mine.

15:45.979 --> 15:48.982
So you don't do this
to Hayden.

15:49.016 --> 15:50.950
You don't do this.
You hear me?

15:53.486 --> 15:56.589
Please.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.958
Put the gun down.

15:58.992 --> 16:05.999
**

16:06.166 --> 16:07.134
[ Sighs ]

16:07.167 --> 16:14.174
**

16:14.274 --> 16:15.808
[ Handcuffs clanking ]

16:15.842 --> 16:18.078
Yeah, I got a pulse.
Call an ambulance.

16:20.680 --> 16:22.682
Jenny: Hey.

16:22.715 --> 16:25.152
Everything's gonna be okay.

16:25.185 --> 16:26.319
No, it's not.

16:26.353 --> 16:27.854
Yes, it is.

16:27.887 --> 16:29.522
You're gonna be okay.

16:29.556 --> 16:31.624
We'll get you the help
that you need, okay?

16:31.658 --> 16:38.531
**

16:38.565 --> 16:45.572
**

16:45.738 --> 16:47.640
Ren: Where's my brother?

16:47.674 --> 16:49.676
Jenny: ICU.

16:49.709 --> 16:51.978
We stabilized him long enough
for the ambulance to arrive.

16:52.011 --> 16:54.547
You're welcome.
Am I supposed to thank you
for doing your job?

16:54.581 --> 16:56.749
[ Chuckles ]

16:56.783 --> 16:58.551
When are you gonna realize
there's no place for you

16:58.585 --> 16:59.852
here in Helena?

16:59.886 --> 17:01.754
Is this "High Noon"?

17:01.788 --> 17:04.391
Am I supposed
to get my black hat?

17:04.424 --> 17:05.692
Your brother got shot
because of what

17:05.725 --> 17:07.094
your family's doing
in this town.

17:07.127 --> 17:09.696
I could have left him
bleeding in the dirt.

17:09.729 --> 17:13.032
Maybe I should have.
Back off.

17:13.066 --> 17:14.334
What about my father?

17:14.367 --> 17:15.868
Can't help you.
It's fine.

17:15.902 --> 17:18.138
I'll have Travis
look into it.

17:21.040 --> 17:23.076
What did you say?
Travis.

17:23.110 --> 17:24.344
Your friend.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.045
I know
he used to be a cop,

17:26.079 --> 17:27.680
but now he works for me.

17:27.714 --> 17:30.049
So helpful.

17:30.083 --> 17:33.086
Man of many talents.

17:33.120 --> 17:34.354
But I think you know that,
right?

17:34.387 --> 17:36.423
I don't know
what you're talking about.

17:36.456 --> 17:39.259
You should ask him about
our friend Bob sometime.

17:39.292 --> 17:43.530
'Cause watching Travis stab him
to keep his own cover --

17:43.563 --> 17:45.132
Whew! -- I'm not really
into surprises,

17:45.165 --> 17:47.167
but that one
really got me.

17:48.768 --> 17:51.171
I sure hope nothing bad
happens to your father.

17:52.739 --> 17:55.074
Dangerous world
out there.

17:55.108 --> 18:02.115
**

18:04.284 --> 18:05.585
I'll go look
into finding your dad.

18:05.618 --> 18:07.587
No, just stay here
with me.

18:07.620 --> 18:14.627
**

18:26.439 --> 18:28.608
Hi.

18:28.641 --> 18:31.411
Hey.

18:31.444 --> 18:33.313
I can't stop thinking
about Richard.

18:33.346 --> 18:36.816
What's gonna happen to him
and that family?

18:36.849 --> 18:38.951
Yeah, I -- I'm just glad
it wasn't worse.

18:38.985 --> 18:40.287
Well,
thanks to you and Jenny.

18:40.320 --> 18:41.988
You did good today.

18:42.021 --> 18:44.824
You can acknowledge that.

18:44.857 --> 18:46.526
Yeah,
it doesn't feel like it.

18:46.559 --> 18:50.863
It's hard to think of anything
that's good lately.

18:53.666 --> 18:57.770
Did I ever tell you about my
first day working for your dad?

18:57.804 --> 19:00.173
No.

19:00.207 --> 19:01.974
Well, I was nervous
'cause I really needed the job

19:02.008 --> 19:04.477
and I just didn't want
to screw up.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.646
So, anyway, he tells me
to get him a cup of coffee.

19:06.679 --> 19:08.147
So I get it for him.

19:08.181 --> 19:10.983
And I make it exactly
the way he likes.

19:11.017 --> 19:12.118
One cream, one sugar.

19:12.151 --> 19:13.320
That's right.

19:13.353 --> 19:14.687
And so I go to give it
to him

19:14.721 --> 19:17.023
and I spill it
all over his lap.

19:17.056 --> 19:19.226
[ Laughs ] Oh, no.

19:19.259 --> 19:21.494
Yes, and I thought, "Well,
it's your first day

19:21.528 --> 19:23.830
and it's also now
your last day."

19:23.863 --> 19:24.931
But you know
what your dad did?

19:26.666 --> 19:28.034
He made a joke.

19:28.067 --> 19:30.637
Mm-hmm. He told me
that he was sorry

19:30.670 --> 19:33.406
that he didn't specify that
he likes his coffee in a cup.

19:33.440 --> 19:35.642
So that became
our thing, you know.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.577
One cream, one sugar,
and in a cup.

19:37.610 --> 19:40.480
In a cup, in a cup.

19:40.513 --> 19:41.848
[ Sighs ]

19:41.881 --> 19:44.183
I really miss him.

19:46.052 --> 19:47.387
And, you know,
with Ronald being gone,

19:47.420 --> 19:50.823
I thought that that was gonna
make some difference.

19:50.857 --> 19:54.093
But it hasn't.
At all.

19:54.126 --> 19:56.396
My dad's still gone
and, somehow,

19:56.429 --> 20:01.601
Scarlet's still out there
with an innocent little girl.

20:01.634 --> 20:03.236
What kind of world
do we live in?

20:03.270 --> 20:05.538
It's okay to talk
about how you feel, honey.

20:05.572 --> 20:08.341
You need to.

20:08.375 --> 20:10.042
Yeah, I've been thinking
about what you said

20:10.076 --> 20:12.078
about the grief counseling,
so...

20:12.111 --> 20:13.446
Well, I just think
it's a good idea.

20:13.480 --> 20:14.447
There are other people
who have gone through

20:14.481 --> 20:16.583
what you've gone through.

20:16.616 --> 20:18.851
Yeah, thank you.

20:18.885 --> 20:20.520
Mm.

20:20.553 --> 20:24.591
**

20:24.624 --> 20:26.459
[ Water running ]

20:34.334 --> 20:36.803
Honey?

20:36.836 --> 20:38.805
What happened to you?

20:38.838 --> 20:40.907
[ Groans ]
You -- You went for a run.

20:40.940 --> 20:42.275
I went for a long walk.

20:42.309 --> 20:43.610
[ Scoffs ]
[ Vehicle door closes ]

20:43.643 --> 20:45.878
You know,
I-I'll explain it later.

20:45.912 --> 20:48.648
Ex-Explain what?

20:50.283 --> 20:53.252
Jag is in the hospital
with a bullet in his chest.

20:54.521 --> 20:56.689
But I'm glad to see
you're okay, Dad.

20:58.325 --> 21:00.460
Honey,
what is she talking about?

21:00.493 --> 21:02.495
Yeah, if you could
fill us all in,

21:02.529 --> 21:04.397
I would love to know
what happened.

21:04.431 --> 21:06.899
Okay, what would you like
to discuss first?

21:06.933 --> 21:09.936
The unavoidable cost
of doing business

21:09.969 --> 21:12.505
or my own family
trying to take me down?

21:12.539 --> 21:15.174
Don't blame Jag
for your mistakes.

21:16.509 --> 21:18.511
I'm blaming both of you.

21:18.545 --> 21:22.615
Plotting behind my back
like rats.

21:24.684 --> 21:27.587
Ah, there it is.

21:27.620 --> 21:31.324
**

21:31.358 --> 21:33.493
See, I had the most
interesting conversation

21:33.526 --> 21:37.497
with your little brother
before our little mishap.

21:37.530 --> 21:40.533
Um, can -- can -- can we all
just take a timeout

21:40.567 --> 21:43.135
and tell me what the hell
this conversation is about?

21:43.169 --> 21:45.304
Reenu can tell you
everything.

21:45.338 --> 21:48.107
Because,
like all of Jagat's ideas,

21:48.140 --> 21:50.176
they take root
in her head.

21:52.745 --> 21:56.616
You know, your mother
had this very same problem.

21:56.649 --> 21:57.850
Don't you dare.

21:59.352 --> 22:01.287
So it wasn't your idea?

22:01.320 --> 22:03.390
Dad.

22:03.423 --> 22:05.625
What happened?

22:05.658 --> 22:07.494
All you need to know
is my time is not over.

22:09.662 --> 22:11.464
We're talking
about your son.

22:11.498 --> 22:13.299
Can't you just admit that
the fact that he got shot

22:13.332 --> 22:16.202
is because you cut our product
with rat poison?

22:16.235 --> 22:20.172
Cutting poison with poison --
what a monstrous idea.

22:20.206 --> 22:24.210
Spare us the sanctimony
and answer me this one question.

22:24.243 --> 22:29.849
When you imagined
taking over my business,

22:29.882 --> 22:31.984
how long did you plan
on stringing

22:32.018 --> 22:35.021
your poor little brother along
before cutting him loose?

22:35.054 --> 22:38.257
What, Reenu, second in line
was never your destiny.

22:38.290 --> 22:40.427
From the moment
Jagat was born,

22:40.460 --> 22:43.162
all he ever did
was get in your way.

22:43.195 --> 22:44.897
I'm done here.
I'm not!

22:44.931 --> 22:49.402
**

22:49.436 --> 22:52.772
You really think
you can do better than me?

22:52.805 --> 22:56.609
I know I can.

22:56.643 --> 23:02.849
**

23:02.882 --> 23:07.286
[ Eric Burdon & The Animals'
"Help Me Girl" plays ]

23:07.319 --> 23:09.522
Mom,
can I have a quarter?

23:09.556 --> 23:11.090
* Girl,
have you ever been hungry *

23:11.123 --> 23:12.759
Maybe next time,
sweetheart.

23:12.792 --> 23:14.561
3. Thank you.
* So hungry

23:14.594 --> 23:15.628
Number 12 to go.
[ Bell dings ]

23:15.662 --> 23:17.096
Come on.

23:17.129 --> 23:20.132
* Well, I've got that feeling

23:20.166 --> 23:21.734
Hurry.

23:21.768 --> 23:23.736
* That biting,
gnawing deep inside *

23:23.770 --> 23:26.706
* It's a funny pain

23:26.739 --> 23:29.742
* One I can't explain

23:29.776 --> 23:31.611
* You gotta help me, girl

23:31.644 --> 23:33.880
Ohh.
Oh, my goodness,
how clumsy of me.

23:33.913 --> 23:34.914
I'm so sorry.

23:34.947 --> 23:36.816
It's fine.
Come on, Phoebe.

23:36.849 --> 23:40.119
Well, at least let me, um,
replace the milkshake.

23:40.152 --> 23:42.321
There's really no need.
We're kind of in a rush, so...

23:42.354 --> 23:44.824
Well,
how 'bout a ride then?

23:44.857 --> 23:46.493
Where ya headed?

23:46.526 --> 23:48.294
Just home.

23:48.327 --> 23:50.129
Is that right?

23:50.162 --> 23:51.964
Where's that?

23:54.133 --> 23:56.903
You know, I'm happy to swing you
wherever you need to go.

23:56.936 --> 23:59.672
Soon as I get my food.

23:59.706 --> 24:03.242
I know I sure get
pretty disagreeable

24:03.275 --> 24:05.512
on an empty stomach.

24:05.545 --> 24:07.046
We're good.

24:09.616 --> 24:10.850
Thanks.

24:10.883 --> 24:13.486
[ Police siren chirps ]

24:13.520 --> 24:20.527
**

24:21.828 --> 24:28.835
**

24:35.141 --> 24:38.377
Jag Bhullar? Right down
the hall? You're kidding me.

24:38.410 --> 24:40.312
Jenny: In way worse shape
than you.

24:40.346 --> 24:41.781
[ Chuckles ]

24:41.814 --> 24:43.182
Richard, how's he?

24:45.417 --> 24:47.053
You're a good man.

24:47.086 --> 24:49.055
Richard shoots you
and you ask how he is?

24:49.088 --> 24:51.023
Well,
Richard's a good man, too.

24:51.057 --> 24:53.292
Or he was.
Hell, I don't know anymore.

24:53.325 --> 24:55.027
[ Chuckles ]

24:55.061 --> 24:58.130
Now, are you gonna tell me
why you're really here?

24:58.164 --> 25:00.132
You got that look
in your eye.

25:00.166 --> 25:03.703
Travis.
He's disappeared.

25:03.736 --> 25:05.304
He checked out
of his motel

25:05.337 --> 25:06.372
and his phone goes
straight to voicemail.

25:06.405 --> 25:07.807
Well,
it's not the first time

25:07.840 --> 25:09.308
we've had trouble
tracking him down.

25:09.341 --> 25:10.577
This is different.

25:10.610 --> 25:12.478
Ren knows he's a cop.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.146
Told me
he switched sides.

25:14.180 --> 25:16.048
Straight up bragged about it
to me.

25:16.082 --> 25:17.817
He's been undercover
for how long,

25:17.850 --> 25:19.719
can't make a case?

25:19.752 --> 25:22.221
He's either terrible at his job
or he's dirty.

25:22.254 --> 25:24.090
Or there's
something else.

25:24.123 --> 25:27.026
Let me guess, something you know
about and aren't telling me?

25:30.763 --> 25:33.032
Well, whatever it is, Jenny,
you need to forget about him.

25:33.065 --> 25:35.501
No, I-I don't think
I could do that.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.236
Well, then try harder.

25:37.269 --> 25:39.706
What if you need
to take him down?

25:39.739 --> 25:41.440
You need to be prepared
for anything, Jenny.

25:41.473 --> 25:43.743
And not just
when it comes to Travis.

25:43.776 --> 25:45.111
Others think the same.

25:46.545 --> 25:48.280
County's bringing someone in
to be acting sheriff

25:48.314 --> 25:50.516
while I'm down.
I'm already acting sheriff.

25:50.549 --> 25:52.018
They just want someone
who has experience

25:52.051 --> 25:53.419
managing a department.

25:53.452 --> 25:55.021
Don't worry,
I'll make sure it's someone

25:55.054 --> 25:56.422
who's a help to you.

25:56.455 --> 25:57.690
I don't need any help.

25:57.724 --> 25:59.458
Yeah, you do.

26:02.228 --> 26:03.129
Okay, fine.

26:05.798 --> 26:06.999
As long
as it's temporary.

26:09.068 --> 26:10.970
No way I'm letting you
go down like this.

26:11.003 --> 26:13.572
Deal.

26:15.942 --> 26:18.077
Oh, hey.

26:18.110 --> 26:19.478
What's with the guard
outside the door?

26:19.511 --> 26:22.649
**

26:22.682 --> 26:24.784
I was here earlier
and there was someone here

26:24.817 --> 26:27.486
that shouldn't have been.
What, you think
the Bhullars?

26:27.519 --> 26:29.155
Could be.

26:29.188 --> 26:30.657
Or possibly
the syndicate.

26:30.690 --> 26:37.697
**

26:40.933 --> 26:45.504
[ Sighs ]
An insurance release for Jag.

26:45.537 --> 26:48.074
They need a family member
to sign it.

26:48.107 --> 26:50.276
Now?
Yes, now.

26:50.309 --> 26:52.845
Just sign it
by the little flaggies.

26:55.715 --> 26:57.316
[ Pages flipping ]

26:57.349 --> 27:02.855
**

27:02.889 --> 27:04.356
You know, you, uh,

27:04.390 --> 27:08.360
still haven't told me
exactly what happened.

27:12.031 --> 27:14.100
Jagat stepped
out of line,

27:14.133 --> 27:16.568
and that comes
with consequences.

27:18.337 --> 27:24.443
Younger generation, as sensitive
and misguided as they are,

27:24.476 --> 27:27.379
they are supposed to pick up
where we left off.

27:27.413 --> 27:29.982
It's what happens.
It's what's supposed to happen.

27:30.016 --> 27:32.484
Well,
my children are not ready.

27:32.518 --> 27:36.655
Every day proves that
more and more.

27:36.689 --> 27:41.160
**

27:41.193 --> 27:42.829
You're the one
who's not ready.

27:42.862 --> 27:46.532
Hmm.

27:46.565 --> 27:48.200
Boy,
I thought you understood.

27:48.234 --> 27:50.903
I thought
you were on my side.

27:50.937 --> 27:52.705
I am.

27:52.739 --> 27:54.173
Good.

27:54.206 --> 27:56.342
Then I don't need
to remind you

27:56.375 --> 27:58.144
that you would be nothing
without me.

27:58.177 --> 28:01.981
Careful, sweetheart.

28:02.014 --> 28:03.883
My love,
like my wise counsel,

28:03.916 --> 28:05.251
has its limits.

28:05.284 --> 28:09.188
Ah, honey,
don't you threaten me.

28:09.221 --> 28:11.223
And right now, I don't want
your wise counsel.

28:11.257 --> 28:13.525
Oh, I'm aware.

28:13.559 --> 28:16.595
But you will listen
to me.

28:16.628 --> 28:19.899
Walk away.

28:19.932 --> 28:22.902
Or you can fight it out
with your children

28:22.935 --> 28:25.237
until your last breath.

28:25.271 --> 28:28.540
Maybe you'll win,
maybe you won't.

28:28.574 --> 28:30.910
But either way,
it will be a future

28:30.943 --> 28:33.079
that does not include me.

28:33.112 --> 28:40.119
**

28:40.319 --> 28:47.293
**

29:10.249 --> 29:13.385
Phoebe: Mom, where are we gonna
sleep tonight?

29:13.419 --> 29:16.155
[ Sighs ]
I don't know yet, sweetheart.

29:16.188 --> 29:17.189
We'll figure it out.

29:20.259 --> 29:21.427
Together.

29:26.799 --> 29:29.035
[ Sighs ]
[ Knock at door ]

29:31.603 --> 29:33.105
Be right out.

29:36.008 --> 29:38.477
[ Harder knock at door ]

29:38.510 --> 29:45.517
**

29:47.019 --> 29:50.356
I said
there's someone in here.

29:50.389 --> 29:52.491
Humbert: Tell me something,
Scarlet.

29:52.524 --> 29:55.161
Do you miss Ronald?

29:55.194 --> 29:59.498
**

29:59.531 --> 30:03.302
Because you're gonna see him
real soon.

30:03.335 --> 30:10.342
**

30:11.343 --> 30:18.350
**

30:19.251 --> 30:21.053
Scarlet.

30:22.654 --> 30:25.657
We know you made a copy
of something

30:25.691 --> 30:27.193
that wasn't yours.

30:27.226 --> 30:31.697
**

30:31.730 --> 30:35.301
You need to tell me
where it is.

30:35.334 --> 30:40.739
Otherwise,
I'll kill Phoebe, too.

30:40.772 --> 30:47.546
**

30:47.579 --> 30:54.553
**

30:54.586 --> 31:01.093
**

31:07.299 --> 31:08.901
My dad died recently.

31:12.604 --> 31:14.873
He was killed.

31:14.907 --> 31:16.475
Murdered, actually.

31:18.978 --> 31:20.846
And, um...

31:20.879 --> 31:24.883
**

31:24.917 --> 31:26.585
...I know I shouldn't be
thinking this way.

31:26.618 --> 31:32.524
**

31:32.558 --> 31:34.826
It hap-- It happened
because of me.

31:36.795 --> 31:38.097
[ Sighs ]

31:40.732 --> 31:42.134
Sorry, I can't.

31:44.136 --> 31:46.472
There's no pressure
to share.

31:46.505 --> 31:48.640
Especially
on your first day.

31:48.674 --> 31:53.412
**

31:53.445 --> 31:55.481
It's okay, I want to.

31:55.514 --> 31:57.616
Go on, then.

31:57.649 --> 31:59.085
Take your time.

31:59.118 --> 32:02.955
**

32:02.989 --> 32:05.391
[ Sighs ]

32:05.424 --> 32:09.461
Whenever I-I think
about my dad being gone

32:09.495 --> 32:12.498
[voice breaking] it hurts
so much...

32:15.534 --> 32:21.273
...that I -- I didn't know
if I could...

32:21.307 --> 32:24.010
**

32:24.043 --> 32:25.744
...stay in the house
that we lived in.

32:25.777 --> 32:28.180
Um... [ Sniffles ]

32:28.214 --> 32:30.949
[ Sighs ]
Then I decided I --

32:30.983 --> 32:36.222
I'm not gonna be chased away
from my home and my job.

32:38.290 --> 32:40.859
The man who killed my dad
isn't gone.

32:40.892 --> 32:43.962
He'll never be gone.

32:43.996 --> 32:47.699
And if I'm being honest,

32:47.733 --> 32:52.338
part of me wants him...

32:52.371 --> 32:54.206
to stay there.

32:55.541 --> 33:00.312
It feels safer, somehow,
to remember the pain.

33:02.681 --> 33:05.617
[ Sighs ] I don't know
if I'm making any sense.

33:05.651 --> 33:07.353
Um...

33:07.386 --> 33:11.657
**

33:11.690 --> 33:13.792
...he's a reminder
to never let my guard down.

33:13.825 --> 33:18.530
**

33:18.564 --> 33:20.132
Yeah.

33:20.166 --> 33:24.002
**

33:26.038 --> 33:28.574
When can we see him?

33:28.607 --> 33:29.708
After Ren.

33:29.741 --> 33:31.077
Family first.

33:33.279 --> 33:35.181
Nice flowers.

33:35.214 --> 33:36.448
I should have
brought something.

33:38.617 --> 33:40.686
You never liked Jag.

33:40.719 --> 33:41.887
I know that.

33:45.424 --> 33:49.061
For the record,
didn't not like.

33:49.095 --> 33:50.996
It's just,
I'm Ren's right hand.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.332
But now he's hurt
and she's sad.

33:53.365 --> 33:54.600
So I'm gonna pretend
to feel something.

34:01.240 --> 34:03.509
Maybe next time
I'll bring a fern.

34:03.542 --> 34:05.944
[ Breathes deeply ]

34:05.977 --> 34:08.013
Maybe it's better
to do nothing.

34:08.046 --> 34:10.082
For now.

34:10.116 --> 34:11.717
There's a lot
to deal with.

34:11.750 --> 34:14.386
Do you mean Stone/Travis,
the cop?

34:14.420 --> 34:16.522
That.

34:16.555 --> 34:18.490
I don't know why Ren
hasn't asked me to kill him yet.

34:22.261 --> 34:23.262
Maybe she has a plan.

34:24.796 --> 34:26.532
I'll await
further instructions.

34:26.565 --> 34:28.134
Yeah.

34:28.167 --> 34:30.736
**

34:30.769 --> 34:33.372
Look at you.

34:33.405 --> 34:36.742
Still handsome
after four hours of surgery.

34:36.775 --> 34:41.180
I heard one of the nurses
talking about your stupid hair.

34:44.483 --> 34:47.119
So I'm gonna make a deal
with you.

34:47.153 --> 34:50.456
You get better

34:50.489 --> 34:53.459
and I'll bring
that stupid beard oil

34:53.492 --> 34:56.962
that you obsess over.

34:56.995 --> 34:59.165
Just don't ask me to rub it in
'cause that would be weird.

35:00.932 --> 35:03.769
Just, um...

35:03.802 --> 35:05.904
make sure it's organic.

35:05.937 --> 35:08.407
Really?

35:08.440 --> 35:10.942
You wake up and the first thing
you do is pick a fight?

35:10.976 --> 35:12.178
[ Both chuckle ]

35:12.211 --> 35:14.746
No.

35:14.780 --> 35:16.148
No more fights.

35:18.350 --> 35:20.452
Agreed.

35:20.486 --> 35:24.423
**

35:24.456 --> 35:25.324
Where's Dad?

35:25.357 --> 35:27.459
Home.

35:28.994 --> 35:30.596
What happened
out there?

35:30.629 --> 35:32.298
He didn't tell you?

35:32.331 --> 35:38.003
**

35:40.172 --> 35:41.707
Miss Hoyt.

35:41.740 --> 35:44.210
We need to pull Travis out.
He's compromised.

35:44.243 --> 35:46.144
I've been telling you that
for weeks.

35:46.178 --> 35:48.013
The Bhullars know
he's a cop.

35:48.046 --> 35:50.849
Miss Hoyt,
are you familiar

35:50.882 --> 35:53.519
with the concept
of collateral damage?

35:53.552 --> 35:54.953
You, of all people,

35:54.986 --> 35:56.788
should understand
that at some point

35:56.822 --> 35:59.325
an asset stops
being an asset

35:59.358 --> 36:02.194
and becomes
a calculated loss.

36:02.228 --> 36:04.496
Are you saying you want
to cut Travis loose?

36:04.530 --> 36:07.666
I'm saying, Travis chose
his own path

36:07.699 --> 36:09.901
and it is not ours
to follow him on it.

36:09.935 --> 36:12.037
You can't be serious. We can't
just abandon one of our own.

36:12.070 --> 36:13.405
The decision
has been made,

36:13.439 --> 36:15.474
and there's nothing
I can do about it.

36:15.507 --> 36:17.876
**

36:17.909 --> 36:20.346
Then I'll do it.

36:20.379 --> 36:23.649
I would strongly advise
against that, Miss Hoyt.

36:23.682 --> 36:27.886
**

36:27.919 --> 36:31.122
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

36:35.694 --> 36:36.862
Hello?

36:38.797 --> 36:40.499
Who is this?

36:40.532 --> 36:42.067
Scarlet: I have information
that you want.

36:44.603 --> 36:46.004
Scarlet?

36:46.037 --> 36:49.275
The girls.
The sex trafficking.

36:49.308 --> 36:50.709
The people Ronald
and the Legarskis

36:50.742 --> 36:53.211
were working with,
I have --

36:53.245 --> 36:55.514
Mom,
I'm hungry.

36:55.547 --> 36:57.048
Okay, sweetheart,
we'll get something soon.

36:57.082 --> 36:58.417
Mommy's on the phone,
okay?

36:58.450 --> 37:01.119
My God, Scarlet,
you still have Phoebe with you?

37:01.152 --> 37:03.555
Yeah, of course I do.
She's my daughter.

37:04.890 --> 37:06.925
I want to make a trade.

37:06.958 --> 37:10.095
Information for a better life
for me and Phoebe.

37:10.128 --> 37:11.730
[ Scoffs ]

37:11.763 --> 37:13.098
That's not how this works.

37:13.131 --> 37:15.367
It can if you make it.

37:15.401 --> 37:18.203
No, you don't get
to walk away.

37:18.236 --> 37:20.606
Wolf told us about his deal
with the syndicate.

37:20.639 --> 37:24.276
If you run, they will find you.
It doesn't matter where.

37:24.310 --> 37:26.378
Mexico, Canada.

37:26.412 --> 37:27.713
Maybe it'll take a year,
maybe longer.

37:27.746 --> 37:29.948
But Phoebe deserves more
out of this life.

37:29.981 --> 37:32.284
Stop trying to scare me.
You should be scared.

37:32.318 --> 37:34.286
You and Ronald killed
innocent people.

37:34.320 --> 37:37.423
You are the furthest thing
from a victim.

37:38.924 --> 37:41.893
You should watch
how you talk to me.

37:41.927 --> 37:43.562
I could come for you.

37:43.595 --> 37:45.664
Oh, I'll be waiting.

37:45.697 --> 37:46.832
You killed...

37:46.865 --> 37:49.635
the love of my life.

37:49.668 --> 37:51.770
I'd do it again.

37:51.803 --> 37:54.606
Give Phoebe up.

37:54.640 --> 37:56.041
It's your only good option.

37:57.609 --> 37:59.611
I could protect her,
Scarlet.

37:59.645 --> 38:01.513
[ Phone clicks ]

38:04.215 --> 38:05.651
Scarlet?

38:05.684 --> 38:06.952
Scarlet?

38:15.561 --> 38:17.629
[ Keys thud ]

38:17.663 --> 38:24.002
**

38:24.836 --> 38:26.605
[ Scoffs ]

38:26.638 --> 38:28.607
We need to stop meeting
like this.

38:28.640 --> 38:31.009
I'm here to say goodbye,
Jenny.

38:31.042 --> 38:33.979
Goodbye?
Travis, Ren knows you're a cop.

38:34.012 --> 38:36.147
We need to get you out
right now.

38:36.181 --> 38:38.484
No.

38:38.517 --> 38:41.186
No, it's just not as simple
as that anymore.

38:41.219 --> 38:42.788
If this is
about you killing Bob,

38:42.821 --> 38:43.789
we'll figure it out.

38:43.822 --> 38:46.558
Ain't about Bob.

38:46.592 --> 38:47.659
Ain't about Ren.

38:51.897 --> 38:53.098
And it ain't
about you and me.

38:54.900 --> 38:57.202
This is about
Kate Garza.

38:57.235 --> 38:59.805
Yeah, I'm gonna see this through
for her.

38:59.838 --> 39:05.043
**

39:05.076 --> 39:06.545
Travis, what --

39:06.578 --> 39:09.481
what about us?

39:09.515 --> 39:13.351
I didn't plan on this.
I didn't plan on us.

39:13.385 --> 39:15.954
[ Whispering ]
Then...don't do this.

39:18.089 --> 39:20.659
I have to.

39:20.692 --> 39:22.694
'Cause this is the only thing
I'm here to do.

39:22.728 --> 39:25.831
[ Deer Tick's
"Goodbye, Dear Friend" plays ]

39:25.864 --> 39:30.536
**

39:30.569 --> 39:32.604
* Some roads that you take

39:32.638 --> 39:34.440
Bye, Hoyt.

39:34.473 --> 39:38.710
* Some bonds we'll choose
to break *

39:38.744 --> 39:40.045
* I swore I'd no longer

39:40.078 --> 39:42.213
I'm still a cop.
I can stop you.

39:42.247 --> 39:44.215
[ Chuckles ]

39:44.249 --> 39:46.051
You're not gonna
shoot me.

39:46.084 --> 39:47.586
* But I carried you to bed

39:47.619 --> 39:50.556
You love me.

39:50.589 --> 39:54.392
Deep down, you always knew you
were gonna have to let me go.

39:54.426 --> 39:59.230
* You were taking off a load
of heavy drinking *

39:59.264 --> 40:00.466
[ Door closes ]

40:00.499 --> 40:02.200
[ Sighs ]

40:02.233 --> 40:05.904
* The world it carries on

40:05.937 --> 40:09.775
* Your memories and song

40:09.808 --> 40:14.980
* And your pictures on my wall
are not forgotten *

40:17.516 --> 40:21.252
* There was hymns
that came from mouths *

40:21.286 --> 40:23.321
* That turned crosses
upside down *

40:23.354 --> 40:25.624
You ready?

40:25.657 --> 40:27.225
I suppose so.

40:27.258 --> 40:28.660
Great.

40:28.694 --> 40:29.628
Jag will be happy
to see you.

40:29.661 --> 40:31.930
We shall see.

40:31.963 --> 40:34.733
You were right.

40:34.766 --> 40:36.468
I have lost a step.

40:36.502 --> 40:39.505
And maybe it is time
I step down,

40:39.538 --> 40:41.272
hand things over.

40:41.306 --> 40:44.142
You know, it's difficult
for a man to admit

40:44.175 --> 40:46.478
he can no longer
do things.

40:46.512 --> 40:49.114
* To think about, but you

40:49.147 --> 40:53.351
I am sorry
for being hard on you, Reenu.

40:53.384 --> 40:56.822
See, I harp on you
for being like your mother

40:56.855 --> 41:00.926
when the truth is
you're more like me.

41:00.959 --> 41:03.795
In every way.

41:03.829 --> 41:05.697
Fierce.

41:05.731 --> 41:08.466
Mm, dogged.

41:08.500 --> 41:11.770
**

41:11.803 --> 41:13.605
Relentless.

41:13.639 --> 41:18.243
I always knew
it would be you.

41:20.345 --> 41:22.380
I just had to see it
for myself.

41:22.413 --> 41:26.518
**

41:26.552 --> 41:29.454
You have done so good,
Reenu.

41:29.487 --> 41:34.359
* In pictures and in song

41:34.392 --> 41:36.361
And I love you.

41:36.394 --> 41:38.530
* And the unmade bed
you slept in *

41:38.564 --> 41:41.733
* Where I laid you down
to rest one last time *

41:41.767 --> 41:42.968
I love you, too, Dad.

41:43.001 --> 41:46.071
* Goodbye

41:46.104 --> 41:48.039
Now let's go see
your son.

41:51.076 --> 41:58.083
* Goodbye, dear friend

41:59.618 --> 42:01.553
Mom.

42:01.587 --> 42:03.521
Where are we?

42:03.555 --> 42:05.490
Just watch your show,
honey.

42:05.523 --> 42:10.862
**

42:10.896 --> 42:12.731
[ Engine starts ]

42:23.642 --> 42:30.649
**

42:31.817 --> 42:38.824
**

42:39.925 --> 42:46.932
**

